text: Expression of <extra_id_0> TLR4 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> Protein Increased in Brain Tissue after ICH

To investigate the increased <extra_id_0> TLR4 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> at the protein level , the expression of <extra_id_0> TLR4 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> protein was measured in brain tissue by the method of Western Blots using specific antibodies for <extra_id_0> TLR4 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> .
Our results showed that a low level of <extra_id_0> TLR4 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> protein was detectable in the saline control group .

The expression of <extra_id_0> TLR4 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> significantly increased starting from 6 hours after ICH ( P < .05 ) , peaked on the 3rd day after ICH , and then decreased but still maintained at a high level on the 7th day after ICH ( P < .05 , Figure 2 ) .
This observation of <extra_id_0> TLR4 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> protein was consistent with the temporal profile of the <extra_id_0> TLR4 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> mRNA after ICH .
